Table description: This dataset shows the Battery Electric Vehicles (BEVs) and Plug-in Hybrid Electric Vehicles (PHEVs) that are currently registered through Washington State Department of Licensing (DOL).
Previous queries:
1. Analyze the distribution of Electric Vehicle Types (BEV, PHEV) in different counties.
2. Explore the correlation between Electric Range and Electric Vehicle Model Year.
3. Investigate the relationship between Electric Vehicle Model and the Electric Utility company associated with the vehicle.
4. Examine the impact of Legislative District on the Clean Alternative Fuel Vehicle (CAFV) eligibility of vehicles.
5. Identify any patterns or trends in the base MSRP (Manufacturer's Suggested Retail Price) of Electric Vehicles.
6. Geospatial analysis to visualize the distribution of Electric Vehicles across different cities in Washington state.
7. Perform clustering analysis to identify groups of Electric Vehicles with similar characteristics.
8. Conduct sentiment analysis on the Clean Alternative Fuel Vehicle (CAFV) eligibility status to gauge public perception.
9. Forecast future growth in Electric Vehicle registrations based on historical data.
10. Conduct association rule mining to discover relationships between different attributes of Electric Vehicles.

Table description:
***Starting on March 7th, 2024, the Los Angeles Police Department (LAPD) will adopt a new Records Management System for reporting crimes and arrests. This new system is being implemented to comply with the FBI's mandate to collect NIBRS-only data (NIBRS — FBI).
During this transition, users will temporarily see only incidents reported in the retiring system. However, the LAPD is actively working on generating new NIBRS datasets to ensure a smoother and more efficient reporting system. ***

******Update 1/18/2024 - LAPD is facing issues with posting the Crime data, but we are taking immediate action to resolve the problem. We understand the importance of providing reliable and up-to-date information and are committed to delivering it.

As we work through the issues, we have temporarily reduced our updates from weekly to bi-weekly to ensure that we provide accurate information. Our team is actively working to identify and resolve these issues promptly.

We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause and appreciate your understanding. Rest assured, we are doing everything we can to fix the problem and get back to providing weekly updates as soon as possible. ****** 


This dataset reflects incidents of crime in the City of Los Angeles dating back to 2020. This data is transcribed from original crime reports that are typed on paper and therefore there may be some inaccuracies within the data. Some location fields with missing data are noted as (0°, 0°). Address fields are only provided to the nearest hundred block in order to maintain privacy. This data is as accurate as the data in the database. Please note questions or concerns in the comments.
Previous queries:
1. Perform data cleaning to address any inaccuracies or missing data present in the dataset.
2. Conduct exploratory data analysis to understand patterns and trends in crime incidents over time and across different areas.
3. Develop predictive models to forecast future crime rates based on historical data.
4. Identify high-crime areas using spatial analysis techniques.
5. Analyze the impact of different crime types on victims based on age, sex, and demographic descent.
6. Create visualizations to effectively communicate key insights from the crime data.
7. Cluster analysis to group similar types of crimes together for further analysis.
8. Determine correlations between crime incidents and various factors such as time of day, location, and crime category.
9. Implement anomaly detection techniques to identify unusual patterns in the crime data.
10. Build a recommendation system for law enforcement agencies to optimize resource allocation based on crime trends and patterns.
